 the 1980s with movies like Rumble Fish, Hammett, Peggy Sue Got Married, to the 1990s and the making of Bram Stoker's Dracula and Kenneth Branagh's Frankenstein, Francis Coppola's career becomes the lens through which Lewis examines the nature of making movies and doing business in Hollywood today.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / Direction & Production.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDuke University Press Archive eBook-Package 1964-1999z978311071360240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780822398981zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780822398981423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780822398981/original  a978-3-11-071360-2  Duke University Press Archive eBook-Package 1964-1999c1964d1999  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles